interestingCommandDescription: Records current position with tags. If position is already recorded it also can modify tags (add "-" in front of a tag to remove it). All positions will have tag called "places".
interestingCommandExample1: /interesting iron ore # records place with tags [iron] and [ore] (and also [place]).
interestingCommandExample2: /interesting cat -dog # records place with tag [cat] and if place is already recorded removes its [dog] tag.
interestingCommandResultNothingToAdd: There are no tags to add.
findInterestingPlaceCommandDescription: Finds a recorded place that has given tags.
noMatchingPlacesFound: No matching places found for tags {0}.
noInterestingTagsFound: There are no records for this place.
editInterestingPlacesCommandDescription: Edits tags in all recorded places around the current position.
editInterestingPlacesCommandExample2: /editInterestingPlaces 0 -home base -> -* # remove all bases except the home base
editInterestingPlacesCommandExample3: /editInterestingPlaces 100 iron -> -iron # remove iron tag from places up to 100 distance away
editInterestingPlacesResultNoPlacesFound: No matching places found within {0} blocks.
copyInterestingPlacesCommandDescription: Copies all recorded places to clipboard.
copyInterestingPlacesCommandExample1: .copyInterestingPlaces # Copy all recorded places to clipboard.
copyInterestingPlacesCommandExample2: .copyInterestingPlaces 10000 -secret base # Copy non-secret bases up to 10k distance away.
pasteInterestingPlacesCommandDescription: Pastes all recorded places from clipboard. Does not remove places. Updates activity periods on tags.
pasteInterestingPlacesCommandExample1: .pasteInterestingPlaces update # Will keep your tags and will add new tags from clipboard.
pasteInterestingPlacesCommandExample2: .pasteInterestingPlaces skip # Will only add new places that you haven't recorded. This is the default.
pasteInterestingPlacesCommandExample3: .pasteInterestingPlaces replace # Will add new places and also replace existing places with tags from clipboard.
